text: Gaius Manlius Valens (AD 6 - 96)Cassius Dio, LXVII.14 was a senator in the Roman Empire. He served with Gaius Antistius Vetus and was elected an ordinary consul.Anthony Birley, The Fasti of Roman Britain (Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1981), p. 230 He died the same year he became consul. == References == Category:6 births Category:96 deaths
title: Gaius Manlius Valens
